All Known Subinterfaces:

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractIntervalXYDataset, AbstractXYDataset, AbstractXYZDataset, CategoryTableXYDataset, CombinedDataset, DefaultBoxAndWhiskerXYDataset, DefaultContourDataset, DefaultHighLowDataset, DefaultTableXYDataset, DefaultWindDataset, DynamicTimeSeriesCollection, EmptyXYDataset, HistogramDataset, JDBCXYDataset, MatrixSeriesCollection, MyXML_XYDataset, NonGridContourDataset, OHLCDataset, SampleSignalDataset, SampleXYDataset, SampleXYDataset2, SampleXYSymbolicDataset, SampleXYZDataset, SampleYSymbolicDataset, SimpleIntervalXYDataset, SimpleIntervalXYDataset2, SubSeriesDataset, TimePeriodValuesCollection, TimeSeriesCollection, TimeTableXYDataset, XYBarDataset, XYSeriesCollection
public interface XYDataset
extends SeriesDataset
An interface through which data in the form of (x, y) items can be accessed.

      Number getXValue​(int series, int item)
      Returns the x-value for an item within a series. The x-values may or may not be returned in ascending order, that is up to the class implementing the interface.

      Returns:
      The x-value (possibly null).
